cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.RO 

This paper focuses on the study of neural homeodynamic responses to environmental changes using both biological and artificial neural networks. The paper discusses the concept of autopoiesis, which is a key concept in the study of living organisms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of artificial neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the autonomous regulation of self and non-self for the network, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.RO (Robotics).
